1. Mega EverDrive PRO/CORE development sources and derived RBF — krikzz
   Upstream: https://github.com/krikzz/mega-ed-pub
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The shipped Mega Drive mapper is built on krikzz's "Mega EverDrive PRO/CORE
Dev Sources", published as libraries, tools and examples for mapper
developers. Rather than copying those sources here, this repository
references upstream as the pinned `references/mega-ed-pub` Git submodule;
`fpga/assemble.py` copies the required files from it locally and applies this
project's modifications from `fpga/patches/achievement-box.patch`. The
assembled files are gitignored, are NOT relicensed under this project's
GPLv3, and remain subject to any terms set by krikzz.

The distributed `fpga/prebuilt/mega-pro.rbf` is an Achievement Box build, not a
binary published by krikzz. It combines the credited Mega EverDrive base and
mapper design with Achievement Box's original WRAM sniffer, telemetry,
controller and console-region logic. Its SHA-256 identity is recorded in
`release-integrity.json`, and its contents and rebuild procedure are
documented in `fpga/RBF-CONTENTS.md` and `fpga/README.md`.

  Original work by THIS project (GPLv3):
    fpga/wram_sniffer.sv
    fpga/pad_watch.sv
    fpga/frame_watch.sv
    fpga/assemble.py

  krikzz files carrying modifications by this project, shipped only as a
  patch (fpga/patches/achievement-box.patch) against the pinned submodule:
    fpga/mapper/lib_base/everdrive.sv
    fpga/mapper/map_smd/hub.sv
    fpga/mapper/map_smd/map_smd.sv
    fpga/fpga_pro/map_smd/mega-pro.qsf

  All other files the Quartus project needs are unmodified krikzz
  dependencies, assembled locally from the submodule and never committed.

